## Section 4: Color System

### 1. Primary Palette

**World Palette**

| Name | Hex | HSL | Meaning | Context |
|------|-----|-----|---------|---------|
| Meadow Green | `#5C8A4D` | 108°, 36%, 41% | Fertility, safety, working land | Default ground tile, meadow biome |
| Earth Brown | `#7A5C3E` | 28°, 34%, 36% | Stability, honest ground | Dirt paths, building foundations |
| Stone Gray | `#8A8B8A` | 0°, 0%, 54% | Permanence, infrastructure | Building walls, stone paths, rock deposits |
| Timber Brown | `#6B5240` | 24°, 32%, 30% | Raw material, medieval handcraft | Building beams, wooden structures, fences |

**Atmosphere / Sky**

| Name | Hex | HSL | Meaning | Context |
|------|-----|-----|---------|---------|
| Dawn Sky | `#C8B8A0` | 36°, 25%, 71% | Beginning of possibility, early optimism | Default sky, early game overlay |
| Overcast | `#A8A8A8` | 0°, 0%, 66% | Bottleneck, stagnation | Bottleneck state overlay |
| Golden Hour | `#D4A85C` | 38°, 58%, 59% | Victory, success, harvest | Victory state, chain completion |

**UI Structural**

| Name | Hex | HSL | Meaning | Context |
|------|-----|-----|---------|---------|
| UI Panel | `#3A3A3A` | 0°, 0%, 23% | UI frame — always present, never competing | Panel backgrounds |
| UI Border | `#5A5A5A` | 0°, 0%, 35% | Edge separating UI from world | Panel borders, button edges |

### 2. Semantic Color Usage

No combat → all semantics are about production chain state.

| Color | Hex | HSL | Meaning | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|---------|-----|
| **Blue** (Action) | `#4A7EA8` | 206°, 39%, 47% | Buildable / Available / "You can do this" | Build preview, placement indicators, action buttons |
| **Golden Yellow** | `#D4A832` | 42°, 66%, 51% | Grain / Raw harvest / Early chain stage | Grain icons, field markers, harvest indicators |
| **Pale Cream** | `#E8DCC4` | 40°, 42%, 84% | Flour / Intermediate stage / Transformation in progress | Flour icons, milling output |
| **Warm Brown** | `#A0724E` | 26°, 35%, 47% | Bread / Final food / Sustenance | Bread icons, bakery output, food storage |
| **Steel Blue** | `#5A7A8E` | 202°, 22%, 42% | Iron ore / Refined metal / Industrial transition | Iron ore icons, mine indicators |
| **Silver Gray** | `#B0B0B0` | 0°, 0%, 69% | Tools / Crafted goods / Mid-level production | Tool icons, toolmaker output |
| **Red** (Error) | `#C45A4A` | 8°, 49%, 53% | Production chain broken / Blocker / Stalled | Build errors, stalled chain markers, low supply warnings |
| **Green** (Success) | `#7DA86B` | 102°, 22%, 56% | Chain complete / Healthy / Available | Chain completion flash, healthy production rate, resource fully stocked |
| **White** (Automated) | `#F0EDE6` | 36°, 18%, 92% | Clean / Refined / Automated stage | Automated zone accents, refined products, automation indicators |

**Red ≠ danger (no combat).** Red = "production chain is broken here." Desaturated terracotta, not fire engine — consistent with medieval architecture. Reserved for genuine problems only.

**Green ≠ background grass.** More orange-shifted than Meadow Green (102° vs 108°), more saturated. Reads as "checkmark" not "lawn."

**Blue = the most colorblind-safe hue.** Used for action states (buildable). No adjustment needed.

### 3. Per-Biome Color Temperature Rules

| Biome | Temperature | Base Ground | Ambient Overlay | Rationale |
|-------|------------|-------------|-----------------|-----------|
| **Meadow** (Early) | Warm (+8 toward yellow) | Meadow Green `#5C8A4D` | Dawn Sky `#C8B8A0` @ 15% | Hope, growth, manual labor — surrounded by nature |
| **Construction Zone** (Mid) | Warm-Metallic (+5 yellow, -5 cool) | Earth Brown `#7A5C3E` | Golden `#D4A85C` @ 10% | Transitional — bridges natural meadow and automated zones |
| **Automated Production** (Late) | Cool-Neutral (-5 toward blue) | Stone Gray `#8A8B8A` | Neutral, slight cool `#B8B8C0` @ 5% | Clean, controlled — cool contrasts sharply with meadow |
| **Settlement Hub** (Center) | Neutral-Warm (baseline) | Earth Brown + Meadow Green patches | None — balanced for UI priority | Player manages everything here; colors must not add cognitive load |

**Lighting State Overlays**

| State | Tint | Opacity |
|-------|------|---------|
| Idle / Neutral | None | 0% |
| Exploration | Cool Dawn `#B8C8D8` | 12% |
| Construction | Warm Morning `#D4A85C` | 10% |
| Production | Bright Midday `#F0E8D0` | 8% |
| Bottleneck | Overcast `#A8A8A8` | 18% |
| Victory | Golden Hour `#D4A85C` | 25% |
| Menu / Dusk | Deep Dusk `#6A6070` | 30% |

### 4. UI Palette

**Divergence from world:** UI deliberately does NOT share hues with world palette. World = warm and earthy; UI = neutral-cool. Ensures UI elements pop without outlines or drop shadows.

**HUD Elements**

| Element | Color | Rationale |
|---------|-------|-----------|
| Resource count numbers | `#F0EDE6` (White) | Max contrast against dark panel |
| Resource icons | Chain colors (golden, cream, brown, steel, silver) | Chain transparency extends to HUD |
| Progress bars | Fill = chain color; Track = `#5A5A5A` | Bars inherit chain meaning |
| Notification badges | `#C45A4A` (Red) + white icon | Only genuine notifications |
| Selection outline | `#4A7EA8` (Blue) 2px stroke | Distinguishable from world |
| Ghost build preview | `#4A7EA8` @ 40% opacity | "Buildable" indicator |
| Invalid build ghost | `#C45A4A` @ 40% opacity | "Cannot build here" |

**Menu Colors**

| Element | Color | Rationale |
|---------|-------|-----------|
| Main menu bg | `#3A3A3A` + Golden Hour sky behind | Sets mood before gameplay |
| Menu title | `#F0EDE6` with `#D4A85C` outline | Golden, prominent |
| Menu buttons (idle) | `#5A5A5A` fill, `#A8A49C` text | Subtle |
| Menu buttons (hover) | `#4A7EA8` fill, `#F0EDE6` text | Action color activates |
| Menu buttons (selected) | `#F0EDE6` fill, `#3A3A3A` text | Max contrast |

### 5. Colorblind Safety

**Critical pair: Red (Error) vs Green (Success) — fails for ALL colorblind types.**

| Problem Pair | Fails For | Severity | Backup Cue |
|-------------|-----------|----------|------------|
| **Red vs Green** | Protanopia, Deuteranopia, Tritanopia | CRITICAL | Triangle icon (error) vs checkmark icon (success). Pulsing (red) vs flash (green). Different shapes. |
| **Green (Meadow) vs Green (Success)** | Deuteranopia, Protanopia | HIGH | Success = checkmark icon + animated pulse. Meadow = no icon, no animation. Different brightness. |
| **Gold (Chain) vs White (Automated)** | Protanopia | MEDIUM | Gold = grain icon. White = clean/refined icon. Luminance: 51% vs 92%. |
| **Brown (Bread) vs Brown (Earth)** | Deuteranopia, Protanopia | MEDIUM | Bread = bread icon. Earth = background, no icon. Different brightness/saturation. |
| **Silver vs Stone** | Protanopia, Deuteranopia | LOW | Silver = tool icon. Stone = background. Different brightness (69% vs 54%). |

**Non-negotiable backup cues:**

| Cue | Examples | Used When |
|-----|----------|-----------|
| Shape/Icon | Triangle = error, Checkmark = success, Sparkle = new, Hourglass = bottleneck | Every semantic color pair that fails colorblind |
| Animation | Pulsing (urgent/red), Flash (event/green), Steady (idle/blue) | Red and green states |
| Pattern | Diagonal lines on red-tinted buildings | Color-only state indicators |
| Sound | Low hum = bottleneck, Ding = success, Chime = construction complete | All notifications |
| Text | "Bottleneck: Grain storage full" | All UI notifications |

**Colorblind modes required:**
- **Protanopia** (red-blind) — ~1% of males
- **Deuteranopia** (green-blind) — ~6% of males
- **Tritanopia** (blue-blind) — ~0.1% of population

**Implementation approach:** No semantic meaning relies on color alone. Production chain uses unique icons (grain stalk, mill wheel, loaf, ore chunk, tool) in addition to color. UI has clear text labels. Sky state overlay works even without color perception.

**Safety adjustments (conditional):**
- If protanopia testing fails: Shift Success Green toward cyan (`#6BAF7A`)
- If protanopia testing fails: Shift Error Red toward orange-red (`#C46A3A`)
- Action Blue (`#4A7EA8`) — safe for all types, no adjustment needed

